<p>Let=E2=80=99s look at the details. We had to order 3 people out of 8. To=
 do this, we started with all options (8) then took them away one at a time=
 (7, then 6) until we ran out of medals.</p>

<p>We know the factorial is:</p>

<p><img src=3D"https://betterexplained.com/wp-content/plugins/wp-latexrende=
r/pictures/24cb43f2a6cb02a29481794d26b0e26a.png" width=3D"202" height=3D"14=
" alt=3D"\displaystyle{ 8! =3D 8 \cdot 7 \cdot 6 \cdot 5 \cdot 4 \cdot 3 \c=
dot 2 \cdot 1 }" class=3D"tex"></p>

<p>Unfortunately, that does too much! We only want <mjx-container class=3D"=
